  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Both the great and the small shall die in this land,.... The nobles as well as the common people, high and low, rich and poor; none shall be exempted from the grievous deaths by the sword, famine, and pestilence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They shall not be buried, neither shall men lament for them; as before, Jeremiah 16:4, this shall be the common case of them all; the great and the rich shall have no more care and notice taken of them than the poor: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "They shall not be buried, neither shall men lament for them; as before, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 16:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", this shall be the common case of them all; the great and the rich shall have no more care and notice taken of them than the poor: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor cut themselves; their flesh, with their nails, or with knives, to show their grief for the dead, and to alleviate the sorrow of surviving friends, by bearing a part with them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor make themselves bald for them; by plucking off the hair of their heads, or by shaving them, and between their eyes; which though forbidden the Jews by the law of God, as being Heathenish customs, yet obtained in the times of Jeremiah, and were usually done; see Deuteronomy 14:1. ",
        "children": [
